From: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Date: Mon, 17 Mar 2025 10:55:22 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: img: Convert to RUNTIME_PM_OPS() and co
Git-commit: 5580e82d222668dd0a484af5612f1d9ae938f075
Patch-mainline: v6.15-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14430 jsc#PED-14297 jsc#PED-14024

Use the newer RUNTIME_PM_OPS() and SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS() macros
instead of SET_RUNTIME_PM_OPS() and SET_SYSTEM_SLEEP_PM_OPS() together
with pm_ptr(), which allows us dropping superfluous CONFIG_PM_SLEEP
ifdefs.

This optimizes slightly when CONFIG_PM is disabled, too.

Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Reviewed-by: Charles Keepax <ckeepax@opensource.cirrus.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250317095603.20073-61-tiwai@suse.de
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>

